---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const projects = [
  {
    title: "AJ's Blog",
    description:
      'This site — a static blog built with Astro, served by nginx, and deployed via GitLab CI.',
    tags: ['Astro', 'TypeScript', 'GitLab CI'],
    url: 'https://gitlab.com/acaylor/ajs-blog',
  },
  {
    title: 'Homelab Infrastructure',
    description:
      'Self-hosted services on Kubernetes across Proxmox servers and Raspberry Pis with automated deployments and monitoring.',
    tags: ['Kubernetes', 'Proxmox', 'ArgoCD'],
    url: '/posts/homelab-2025-plans',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout title="About">
  <div class="container about-page">
    <section class="intro">
      <div class="avatar-area">
        <img src="/images/whoami/whoami.png" alt="Profile photo" class="avatar" />
      </div>
      <div class="intro-text">
        <h1>About</h1>
        <p class="bio">
          This site is a personal blog focused on software, technology, and the cloud. The main
          purpose of this blog is to share what technology I am working with at home.
        </p>
        <div class="links">
          <a href="https://github.com/acaylor" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
          <a href="https://gitlab.com/acaylor" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitLab</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-content">
      <h2>Author</h2>
      <p>
        I am currently a Senior Platform Engineer. I enjoy working with the latest technology in my
        homelab.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="contact" class="contact">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Comments are no longer available on posts. I noticed the platform added nasty advertisements
        and there was no engagement in the comments. If you have a question, feedback, or just want
        to say hello, feel free to reach out.
      </p>
      <div class="contact-methods">
        <a href="mailto:ayyyj@icloud.com" class="surface-card contact-card">
          <svg
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            width="20"
            height="20"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            ><rect width="20" height="16" x="2" y="4" rx="2"></rect><path
              d="m22 7-8.97 5.7a1.94 1.94 0 0 1-2.06 0L2 7"></path></svg
          >
          <div>
            <strong>Email</strong>
            <span>ayyyj@icloud.com</span>
          </div>
        </a>
        <div class="surface-card contact-card">
          <svg
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            width="20"
            height="20"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            ><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle><path d="M8 12h8"></path><path d="M12 8v8"
            ></path></svg
          >
          <div>
            <strong>Discord</strong>
            <span>.ayyj</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-content">
      <h2>Homelab History</h2>
      <p>
        My "lab" began with the first model Raspberry Pi while I was in school. I made a version of
        the classic game Snake in Java, compiled it into a jar, and put it on the Pi with an Apache
        web server so I could download it on other machines. Then I set up a proxy tunnel to my
        network so I could access it from anywhere.
      </p>
      <p>
        That got me hooked on networking and self-hosting. I set up an Ubuntu NAS with SMB and moved
        everything off the Pi. In school we used Java until the end when I had a web dev class that
        was all ASP.NET. My first full-stack app was a meal preparation app with a database of
        recipes that was my final capstone project at university. That was also one of the first
        projects where I used
        <code>git</code> to collaborate with other people.
      </p>
      <p>
        My first job in tech was a mix of Windows AD infrastructure and a large fleet of Linux
        machines for HPC. I set up a home lab on a Dell PowerEdge R610 with ESXi and Windows VMs for
        an Active Directory lab. My second job was all Linux, and every one after has been too.
        Around 2018 I switched to Proxmox hypervisors and TrueNAS (formerly FreeNAS) for storage.
        Later jobs centered on Kubernetes app deployment, so the lab followed with Ubuntu VMs
        running k8s clusters.
      </p>
      <p>Today the setup includes:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>UniFi UDM Pro with cameras and switches</li>
        <li>Synology NAS (12 TB) + backup NAS (4 TB)</li>
        <li>4 Proxmox servers</li>
        <li>5 Raspberry Pis</li>
        <li>Linux server with Nvidia GPU</li>
        <li>M4 Mac mini</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        This uses a lot of power and I would likely not have this many servers without solar to
        offset the cost. I use Wireguard for remote access and a password manager for credentials.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="projects">
      <h2>Projects</h2>
      <div class="project-grid">
        {
          projects.map((project) => {
            const isExternal = project.url.startsWith('http');
            return (
              <a
                href={project.url}
                class="surface-card project-card"
                {...(isExternal ? { target: '_blank', rel: 'noopener noreferrer' } : {})}
              >
                <h3>{project.title}</h3>
                <p>{project.description}</p>
                <div class="project-tags">
                  {project.tags.map((tag) => (
                    <span class="tag-pill">{tag}</span>
                  ))}
                </div>
              </a>
            );
          })
        }
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <style>
    .about-page {
      padding-top: 3rem;
      padding-bottom: 3rem;
      max-width: var(--content-width);
    }

    .intro {
      display: flex;
      gap: 2rem;
      align-items: flex-start;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .avatar {
      width: 6rem;
      min-width: 6rem;
      height: 6rem;
      border-radius: 50%;
      object-fit: cover;
      border: 2px solid var(--color-border-light);
    }

    .intro-text h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: -0.025em;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    .bio {
      font-size: 1.0625rem;
      color: var(--color-text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .links {
      display: flex;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .links a {
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      font-weight: 500;
    }

    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .intro {
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: center;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .links {
        justify-content: center;
      }
    }

    .about-content {
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .about-content h2 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      margin-top: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    .about-content h2:first-child {
      margin-top: 0;
    }

    .about-content p {
      font-size: 1.0625rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    }

    .about-content ol {
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      color: var(--color-text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .contact {
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .contact h2 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    .contact > p {
      font-size: 1.0625rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: var(--color-text-secondary);
      margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    }

    .contact-methods {
      display: grid;
      gap: 1rem;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(14rem, 1fr));
    }

    .contact-card {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.875rem;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    }

    .contact-card svg {
      flex-shrink: 0;
      color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
    }

    .contact-card strong {
      display: block;
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 0.125rem;
    }

    .contact-card span {
      font-size: 0.8125rem;
      color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    }

    .projects h2 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    }

    .project-grid {
      display: grid;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .project-card h3 {
      font-size: 1rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
    }

    .project-card p {
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      color: var(--color-text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.5;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    .project-tags {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.375rem;
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
